cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is about a hybrid dialog state tracker for slot-filling dialog systems, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves rule-based systems, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper uses the Dialog State Tracking Challenge (DSTC) 2 dataset, which is related to natural language processing and machine learning, and could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
